      "writtenOn": "2020-02-19T14:32:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We have a bunch of calls in GrVkGpu that wrap GrBackendTextures and GrBackendRenderTargets. Each of these calls should be checking the usage values. I think each call calls some versions of check_image_info, check_rt_image_info, or check_texture_image_info. To match our current requirements for images, I think check_image_info should fail if trans_src/dst isn\u0027t on the usage flags. check_rt should fail if renderable isn\u0027t on the usage flags. And check_tex should fail if sampled isn\u0027t on the usage flags.",
      "range": {
